---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="What is ABC Prioritization | toADHDo">
  <div
    class="relative w-full mx-auto min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-indigo-900 via-purple-900 to-blue-900 p-4 sm:p-8"
  >
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto flex flex-col md:flex-row gap-4 md:gap-6 items-start">
      <!-- Main Content Card -->
      <div
        class="relative w-full backdrop-blur-xl bg-gradient-to-b from-white/10 to-white/5 rounded-2xl shadow-2xl p-6 sm:p-8 text-white border border-white/10 order-2 md:order-1"
      >
        <div class="space-y-8">
          <div class="text-center">
            <h1
              class="text-4xl sm:text-6xl font-bold mb-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 via-purple-200 to-pink-200 text-transparent bg-clip-text drop-shadow-lg"
            >
              ABC Prioritization System
            </h1>
            <p class="text-lg sm:text-xl text-blue-100/90 drop-shadow-md">
              A time-based priority system designed specifically for people with ADHD
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="flex flex-col gap-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
            <!-- Navigation Buttons -->
            <div class="w-full flex flex-row gap-4 md:gap-6">
              <a
                href="/"
                class="flex-1 px-6 py-4 text-md bg-white/10 hover:bg-white/20 rounded-md text-white font-medium border border-white/10 transition-colors text-center shadow-md"
              >
                Back to Home
              </a>
              <a
                href="/register"
                class="flex-1 px-6 py-4 text-md bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 rounded-md text-white font-medium border border-blue-600/30 transition-colors text-center shadow-md"
              >
                Try toADHDo
              </a>
            </div>

            <div
              class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white/10 to-white/5 backdrop-blur-lg rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/10"
            >
              <h2
                class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 to-purple-200"
              >
                What is the ABC System?
              </h2>
              <p class="text-blue-100/90 leading-relaxed">
                The ABC prioritization system is a time-based approach to organizing tasks, helping individuals with
                ADHD focus on what truly matters. By categorizing tasks based on urgency and importance, it reduces
                decision paralysis and makes planning more manageable.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white/10 to-white/5 backdrop-blur-lg rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/10"
            >
              <h2
                class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 to-purple-200"
              >
                The Three Categories
              </h2>
              <ul class="space-y-4">
                <li class="space-y-2">
                  <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
                    <span class="font-mono bg-red-800/50 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-red-200 shadow-sm text-xl">A</span>
                    <span class="text-blue-100/90 font-semibold">Today or Tomorrow</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="text-blue-100/90 pl-10">
                    Category A tasks are the most important ones with short deadlines. These are your "must-do" items
                    that need immediate attention or will quickly become urgent. Start your planning with these tasks,
                    distributing them according to your energy levels.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li class="space-y-2">
                  <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
                    <span class="font-mono bg-yellow-700/50 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-yellow-200 shadow-sm text-xl">
                      B
                    </span>
                    <span class="text-blue-100/90 font-semibold">This Week</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="text-blue-100/90 pl-10">
                    Category B tasks are less urgent but still important. They can be completed over a longer period,
                    though some stages might need quick action. Plan these after you've scheduled your A tasks.
                  </p>
                </li>
                <li class="space-y-2">
                  <div class="flex items-center space-x-3">
                    <span class="font-mono bg-green-800/50 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg text-green-200 shadow-sm text-xl">
                      C
                    </span>
                    <span class="text-blue-100/90 font-semibold">Longer Term</span>
                  </div>
                  <p class="text-blue-100/90 pl-10">
                    Category C tasks are the least critical. They have no specific deadline, might be less exciting, or
                    simply less important than A and B tasks. Be careful - these can sometimes seem more attractive or
                    easier to complete, but they shouldn't distract you from higher-priority items.
                  </p>
                </li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div
              class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white/10 to-white/5 backdrop-blur-lg rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/10"
            >
              <h2
                class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 to-purple-200"
              >
                How to Implement ABC Prioritization
              </h2>
              <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal pl-5 text-blue-100/90">
                <li>List all tasks you need to complete for the day/week/month</li>
                <li>Assign each task a category (A, B, or C) based on urgency and importance</li>
                <li>Begin planning by scheduling A tasks first, distributing them according to your energy levels</li>
                <li>Add B tasks where they fit best after A tasks are scheduled</li>
                <li>Keep C tasks in your backlog to work on when higher priority items are complete</li>
                <li>Move incomplete tasks to the next day's list and cross off completed ones</li>
                <li>Review and update your list daily to stay on track</li>
              </ol>
              <p class="text-blue-100/90 mt-4">
                When starting out, limit yourself to 2-3 priority tasks and reserve dedicated time for them. Before
                committing to other plans, ask yourself if they align with your top priorities for the day.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div
              class="bg-gradient-to-br from-white/10 to-white/5 backdrop-blur-lg rounded-xl p-6 border border-white/10"
            >
              <h2
                class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4 text-transparent bg-clip-text bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 to-purple-200"
              >
                Tips for Success
              </h2>
              <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 text-blue-100/90">
                <li>Avoid listing all tasks as category A - this defeats the purpose of prioritization</li>
                <li>
                  Don't mix 5-minute tasks with 3-hour tasks on the same list - it distorts your perception of available
                  time
                </li>
                <li>Use a "time container" for small tasks that can be batched together</li>
                <li>Add time buffers (15-30 minutes) between tasks to account for transitions</li>
                <li>Personalize the system - use colors instead of letters if that works better for you</li>
                <li>Be patient with yourself as you adapt to this new way of planning</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="text-lg text-center text-blue-100/90 mt-8 leading-relaxed">
            Ready to try a task management app that helps you implement the ABC system? <br class="hidden sm:block" />
            <a
              href="/register"
              class="font-semibold bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-200 to-purple-200 text-transparent bg-clip-text hover:underline"
            >
              Create an account today and start prioritizing effectively!
            </a>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
